item.title: The World's Biggest IPO Market Is Not Healthy
item.description: The initial public offering (IPO) market is a key barometer of the health of the global economy. In recent years, China has emerged as the dominant player in this market, with the number of IPOs in the country surging while the US and other regions have seen a decline.
